summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeIntroducing New! Anastasia Beverly Hills Brow Freeze Gel, an innovative clear brow wax-gel hybrid featuring a dual action comb applicator that shapes, sculpts and sets brows with extreme hold and precision on-the-go. Achieve lifted, laminated-look brows with hair-loving frozen technology.
details: DetailsBenefitsDual-action comb applicator for versatile brow stylingMicro-bristles grip each hair for maximum separation and fullnessExtreme-staying power for long-lasting holdInstantly creates the look of lifted and feathered browsTravel-friendly, on-the-go applicationDermatologist testedCruelty freeKey IngredientsExtreme-hold and a non-sticky, flake-free texture with Polyacrylate-2 CrosspolymerHydrated effect with GlycerinFormulated WithoutParabensPhthalatesMineral oilFragranceItem 2620491How To UseUse alone or as the finishing step in your brow routine to lock brows in place. Start by using the long bristle comb to separate and tame hair, next use the short bristle comb to shape and sculpt hairs into place. For a laminated-look, use the side of the applicator to lay brow hair down seamlessly.IngredientsWater/Aqua/Eau, Alcohol Denat., Hydroxyethyl Acrylate/Sodium Acryloyldimethyl Taurate Copolymer, Polyacrylate-2 Crosspolymer, Glycerin, Tromethamine, Sorbitol, Acrylates Copolymer, Panthenol, Polysorbate 60, Sorbitan Isostearate, Butylene Glycol, Citric Acid, Allantoin, Ethylhexylglycerin, Sodium Pca, Sodium Lactate, Arginine, Aspartic Acid, Propylene Glycol, Pca, Biotin, Pelvetia Canaliculata Extract, Laminaria Digitata Extract, Glycine, Alanine, Serine, Threonine, Valine, Isoleucine, Proline, Histidine, Phenylalanine, 1,2-Hexanediol, Caprylyl Glycol, Benzoic Acid, Myristoyl Pentapeptide-17, Sodium Benzoate, PhenoxyethanolShipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Use alone or as the finishing step in your brow routine to lock brows in place. Start by using the long bristle comb to separate and tame hair, next use the short bristle comb to shape and sculpt hairs into place. For a laminated-look, use the side of the applicator to lay brow hair down seamlessly.

reviews.headline: Gives a strong hold on brows
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This definitely freezes your brows. I appreciate hold in my brow gel but this might have been a bit too stiff and shiny for my preference. I will continue to use and decide if I want to rebuy. If you like hold this will work for you!

reviews.headline: The BEST brow product!
reviews.comments: I have tired all of the brow products on the market and I can say this is the only one that actually works all day! I have pretty thick eyebrow hairs and love a laminated look that doesn't fake or leave residue. Definitely would recommend this brow product to anyone!

reviews.headline: So good!
reviews.comments: I put this on at 7 a.m. and my eyebrows were still good at 9 p.m. after working a full day in healthcare, taking a nap, and being outside in 100 degree Arkansas weather! My eyebrows looked naturally placed and not slicked down.

reviews.headline: Stays on
reviews.comments: Loved this product because it actually holds my eyebrow in place for the day. I usually wear nyx brow glue because its cheaper but this is a much cleaner product. I think its worth the upgrade. Depending on your budget, both do a great job for their price.

reviews.headline: Only product that works!!!!
reviews.comments: My brows are naturally on the thicker side but fall flat without some shaping. This is the only product out of many that I have tried that holds them in place all day without getting flaky or leaving a shiny cast. I use it literally every day whether or not I'm doing any other makeup and it instantly makes me look more awake and lifted. Cannot recommend it enough!!

reviews.headline: The eyebrows shadows stays
reviews.comments: I think it is a good product however I am more int the natural look eyebrows. So I don't really use gel on them, but I tried this one and they look really good. But you feel it hard. When you move your face you feel there is something on your eyebrows. But it helped me keeping the shadows I usually use on them. Which is perfect for summer I don't have to reapply

reviews.headline: Love!!
reviews.comments: Okay‚Äîso I finally got my hands on the Anastasia Brow Freeze and honestly? It gets the hype. This stuff is like brow glue but in the best possible way. No white residue, no crunchiness‚Äîjust lifted, laminated-looking brows that stayed in place through errands, heat, and even a quick face mist moment.

reviews.headline: Love!!
reviews.comments: Okay‚Äîso I finally got my hands on the Anastasia Brow Freeze and honestly? It gets the hype. This stuff is like brow glue but in the best possible way. I scooped out the tiniest amount (a little seriously goes a long way), pressed it into my brows with a spoolie, and they did not budge all day. reviews.headline: Brow
reviews.comments: Anastasia Beverly Hills brow freeze gel is one of the best eyebrow gels I've ever tried. The application technique is perfect, and it gives a lot of volume to your eyebrows.

reviews.headline: Great hold but flakes off and leaves white marks
reviews.comments: It does a good job of holding the shape and freezing your brows, but the applicator is not my favorite as it traps a lot of product on it and squishes it around. It ends up putting too much on my brows leading to flakey white spots.

reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I love this brow product a lot more than my other brow products honestly because it doesn't leave them sticky or hard. It wear great all day and is my go to product every day now.

reviews.headline: Definite recommend
reviews.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review.The Anastasia brow gel work beautiful! It holds my brows in place without leaving a visible film over them like other brands. No need to reapply more than once in a night! No strong smells on this product which is always a plus.

reviews.headline: Good
reviews.comments: Good product, long lasting. Thin lines. I will buy again and recommend to friends. Neat packaging.

reviews.headline: great hold but lots of residue
reviews.comments: i got this product a couple days ago and the hold is very good the only con i would say about this product is the residue it leaves, and its alot of it.

reviews.headline: Definitely keeps brows in place
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I've used a few brow gels and waxes when I get my eyebrows tinted to keep them from going all over the place. This gel has a glue-like consistency and definitely works. The applicator has two sides that have different sized bristles which I found very convenient. I also absolutely love the velvety feel of the tube for some reason! I received this product complimentary in exchange for my honest review.

reviews.headline: Better Than the Original
reviews.comments: This really keeps the brows in place and I like it a lot better than the formula that came potted. It has a tendency to flake & the formula is pretty wet. I personally prefer a more dry formula. It does hold those hairs though! I think it's worth trying.

reviews.headline: good product
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] this product is very easy to apply. I would definitely recommend and buy again. the ingredients are good on the brow and easy to remove. it makes great curls

reviews.headline: Just alright
reviews.comments: The pro is that it definitely freezes brows without feeling too stiff. The con is the wand part is off in my opinion. Way too clumpy going on. Im going to return, I wish they would make one with a different wand/brush that allows less product when applying.

reviews.headline: Lamination in a stick!
reviews.comments: Anastasia Brow Freeze gel keeps brows lifted and in place all day. It gives a strong hold without feeling stiff or flaky. Easy to apply and perfect for a laminated brow look.

faceoff_positive.comments: I am so happy that I got to try this. I have been looking for a Miracle brow product for over 10 years now. Every single thing I've tried was either too crunchy, too waxy, too slimy, too hard, too soft, didn't last, or just didn't work! I really did not have high hopes for this because it says the word freeze which is typically a red flag for me because that means "hard" or "flakey". This is far from hard or flakey yet it holds the brows like you would a newborn baby! It is not moving! You protect that baby with your life and this will protect your brows with its life LOL! But for real‚Ä¶.. IT IS INCREDIBLE!!! I cannot believe how good this is. It is so natural looking yet it will last 24 hours if you need it too. I have sparse brows and it actually makes them look fuller which shocks me as I can't see the gel when it's on even though it's on really good! It's not hard, it's not shiny, it doesn't get flaky, etc. I'm so glad I got to try this because it blew my mind. I've tried almost every single brow product on the market from high-end to drugstore and there was always one thing that I didn't like about each product that made me have to keep searching. For the first time in my life, I found perfection. This is everything I've ever wanted.i want to purchase 20 of them just in case it ever gets replaced by the brand in 20 years because I never want to be without this.  I don't know what they put in this but it's a miracle worker. Also a massive bonus is that it's huge! My regular AB brow gel never lasted very long and seemed to run out fast to the point I had to purchase one every month or so. This bad boy will last months minimum! Thank you so much for letting me try this. Up until now, the regular OG brow gel was my top brow product but this is replacing that! Hands down 10/10! It's like the OG brow gel but on steroids :)
faceoff_positive.headline: Best brow gel

faceoff_negative.comments: I recieved this product from Bzzagent for testing purposes.  From my understanding  this is a tube version of Anastasia brow wax which I have used and the brow wax is a great product.  So I was excited to recieve this.  ABS has amazing brow products that perform incrediably well, but this isnt one of them.  Overall the product works and will hold your brows in place.  However, after is dries and has been on for a while it leaves a weird whitish residue that isnt cute.  Not to mention I am not a fan of the spoolie you use for application.  You definately have to wipe excess off before taking it to your brow.  Even then it applies more than I would like for it to.  I would prefer to have the ability to do thin lite coats, and add more if needed.  I had the best luck applying with a thin width flat or angled eyeliner brush and running a clean spoolie thru my eyebrows right after to achieve a workable application.  Even after all that extra work the white residue came out 2 hours later or less. I have tried using less product, different brow pencils, pomades, powders and any other brow product I thought I could put on top of it, and I could not make this work without that residue haunting my existence.  If you are going to use it for photos and remove after, it will work and look nice.  If your a normal person that needs thier makeup to look presentable for longer than four hours I recommend using the traditonal wax, or another product.
faceoff_negative.headline: I have mixed feelings
